results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #1
results.description: Jack Kirby set the standard for massive monster mayhem covers before the super hero boom. So bringing those elements together? Magical.

textObjects.text: The Fantastic Four spring to action as a team for the first time. As they learn how to control their new found powers, will it be enough to stop the fury of the Mole Man?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #2
results.description: The First Appearance of the Skrulls!  THE SKRULLS ATTACK EARTH! From deep in space comes the Skrulls. A shape-changing alien race with one goal, to destroy the Fantastic Four and conquer Earth. Can Reed Richards come up with a plan to stop them in time?

items.name: The Fantastic Four Meet the Skrulls from Outer Space!
The Fantastic Four Pin-Up Page Featuring in this Issue: The Thing

textObjects.text: The Fantastic Four has now become world heroes! See the super family get their costumes for the first time.
The Fantastic Four has now become world heroes! See the super family get their costumes for the first time.

items.name: Chapter 1 The Menace of the Miracle Man
Chapter IV "In the Shadow of Defeat!"

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #4
results.description: The First Marvel Age Appearance of Namor!  The Sub-Mariner has returned! Calling upon his mighty sea creature army, he will have his revenge on the human race. It's up to the Fantastic Four to stop him.

textObjects.text: The Sub-Mariner has returned!  Calling upon his mighty sea creature army, he will have his revenge on the human race. It's up to the Fantastic Four to stop him.

stop him.

items.name: The Coming of... Sub-Mariner! Chapter 1 "On the Trail of the Torch!"

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #5
results.description: Doctor Doom, in his very First Appearance!  The Fantastic Four's greatest nemesis is introduced in the first of many titanic battles as Victor Von Doom is out to prove that all should bow before Doom!

textObjects.text: Let's see, what's the most awesome thing about this issue? The first apearance of Dr. Doom? Thing wearing an eyepatch, pretending to be a pirate? Yeah, it's all pretty great.

Let's see, what's the most awesome thing about this issue? The first apearance of Dr. Doom? Thing wearing an eyepatch, pretending to be a pirate? Stan Lee and Jack Kirby starting to hit their stride? Yeah, it's all pretty great.
The Fantastic Four, has met their match. Doctor Doom, has come to make short work of our super family four.
Doctor Doom and the Sub-Mariner have joined forces to stop the Fantastic Four once and for all. But can the Sub-Mariner's hatred of all humans be tamed by the beauty of Sue Storm?
Doctor Doom and the Sub-Mariner have joined forces to stop the Fantastic Four once and for all. But can the Sub-Mariner's hatred of all humans be tamed by the beauty of Sue Storm?

items.name: Captives of the Deadly Duo! Part 1

textObjects.text: The Fantastic Four journey across the cosmos to Planet X. This planet on the edges of spaces needs our heroes help to save it from utter destruction.
The Fantastic Four journey across the cosmos to Planet X. This planet on the edges of spaces needs our heroes help to save it from utter destruction.

items.name: Prisoners of Kurrgo, Master of Planet X Part 1 "It Came From the Skies!"

textObjects.text: The Puppet Master has arrived to control the Fantastic Four. What horrible things does he plan to do? And will our four heroes let the Puppet Master pull the strings that just may rip the family apart?

The Puppet Master has arrived to control the Fantastic Four. What horrible things does he plan to do? And will our four heroes let the Puppet Master pull the strings that just may rip the family apart?

items.name: "The Hands of the Puppet Maker" Part 2

textObjects.text: When the Fantastic Four go bankrupt, they're invited to S.M. Studios to make the movie about their life in order to recoup their funding. Little do they know that S.M. Studios is owned by one of their greatest enemies!

items.name: The End of the Fantastic Four!

textObjects.text: Dr. Doom impersonates Reed Richards so that he may use Richards' shrink ray to finally defeat the Fantastic Four!
At last the Fantastic Four meet a foe whose power is even greater than theirs! Here is: The Impossible Man!

items.name: A Visit with the Fantastic Four

textObjects.text: General Ross tasks the Fantastic Four with finding and capturing the Hulk. But treachery is afoot and the Hulk sets out to find the real villain of the day...the Wrecker!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #13
results.description: The enigmatic Watcher makes his debut in this very issue!  On a mission to the moon, the Fantastic Four meet Uatu, better known as the Watcher, who is tasked to watch humanity but never intervene in their affairs.  And on the way to the moon, the FF see a nearby Russian ship being hit by cosmic rays and the Russian crew are affected in a startling way!

textObjects.text: More than two hundred thousand miles from Earth, the Fantastic Four face the menace of The Red Ghost!

items.name: The Fantastic Four Versus the Red Ghost and His Indescribable Super-Apes

textObjects.text: The Puppet Master has gained control over the Sub-Mariner and hatches a plan to finally ensnare and defeat the Fantastic Four.
The Fantastic Four battle the Mad Thinker and his awesome Android! The Android...neither animal, nor vegetable, nor mineral...what is it?!

items.name: The Fantastic Four Battle the Mad Thinker and His Awesome Android
A Gallery of the Fantastic Four's Most Famous Foes

textObjects.text: The first appearance of Rama-Tut, later revealed to be Kang the Conqueror!
The enigmatic Hate-Monger uses his hate ray to break up the Fantastic Four! Can Marvel's First Family overcome this mysterious enemy's strange ability? Guest-starring Nick Fury!
The Fantastic Four's first foe returns with a vengeance! The mighty Mole Man's plan is to sink the world's largest cities down to his level, and he already has a plan to deal with the FF!

items.name: The Return of the Mole Man

textObjects.text: The diabolical Dr. Doom gathers a new super-villain group, the Terrible Trio! Can the Fantastic Four defeat their greatest nemesis when he's backed by his own team?

items.name: The Master Plan of Doctor Doom

textObjects.text: A strange extra-terrestrial being is wreaking havoc on Earth! The FF must deal with a threat the likes of which they've never faced before: the Infant Terrible!
The battle you've been waiting for! The Incredible Hulk vs. the Ever Lovin' Blue-Eyed Thing! Nuff said!
The Hulk continues his rampage through New York City, but the Avengers have arrived to challenge their former member. Can the FF and Earth's Mightiest Heroes work together to stop the Jade Giant?
The Invisible Girl is kidnapped by Namor the Sub-Mariner, Prince of Atlantis! The remaining members of the Fantastic Four enlist the aid of Doctor Strange to expedite their rescues efforts!
The X-Men guest-star as they and the Fantastic Four face the combined menace of the Puppet Master, Mad Thinker, and the Awesome Android!

items.name: We Have to Fight the X-Men!

textObjects.text: The Fantastic Four enter into a rematch against the Red Ghost and his Super-Apes! Guest-starring the Watcher!

results.title: Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #2
results.description: A special double-sized issue! Double the action! Double the terror! Doctor Doom has the Fantastic Four right where he wants them. Will the FF be able to stand against their menace? Also featuring the twisted back story of Doctor Doom, the Fantastic Four's cruelest nemesis to date.

items.name: The Fantastic Origin of Doctor Doom
A Gallery of the Fantastic Four's Most Famous Foes
The Final Victory of Doctor Doom

textObjects.text: Witness the debut of the adept alchemist Diablo. Is this mysterious new superhuman friend or foe? And can he succeed in curing the Thing where Reed failed?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #31
results.description: The Mole-Man emerges from his underground lair to bait the Fantastic Four into battle! Will the team be able to withstand his legion of Mole People? A very strange smack-down ensues.

items.name: The Mad Menace of the Macabre Mole Man

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #32
results.description: Who exactly is the Invincible Man? What beef does he have with the Fantastic Four? And just how invincible is this new villain? A hero will fall in this shocking issue.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #33
results.description: A new development for the Fantastic Four! The team joins Namor, the Sub-Mariner, to take down an aquatic foe that is causing trouble in Atlantis. Will Namor have the audacity to flirt with the Invisible Woman in front of Mr. Fantastic?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #34
results.description: Super-villain Gideon has pitted the Fantastic team against each other! When your best asset is team-work, what chance do you stand divided? Sibling against sibling, friend against friend!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #35
results.description: The Fantastic Four go back to school! But not to pursue undergraduate studies. When the Dragon Man unleashes chaos on a college campus, will the FF be able to save the co-eds in his path of destruction?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #36
results.description: The Frightful Four versus the Fantastic Four! The Wizard! Medusa! Sand Man! Trapster! Will the FF be overpowered by the brawn and brains of their toughest foes yet?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #37
results.description: In their exploration, the Fantastic Four have ended up on a distant planet in a remote galaxy. But when they encounter the natives will the meeting be friendly...or sinister? A galactic adventure that opens a new can of worms for the super team!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #38
results.description: The Frightful Four return, and this time they've brought their A-game. The villains have managed to strand the FF without resources! Are the Fantastic Four truly defeated?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #39
results.description: Daredevil and the FF! The blind super hero won't need his sight to lead the team. But why have the superheroes combined forces? Is it because of Doctor Doom's ominous return?

items.name: A Blind Man Shall Lead Them

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #40
results.description: Daredevil continues to fight alongside the FF in defense of the Baxter Building. Will the super team be rudely evicted from their home...by Doctor Doom?

items.name: The Battle of the Baxter Building

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #41
results.description: The brutal betrayal of Ben Grimm! The Frightful Four kidnap the Thing and force him into helping them defeat the rest of his team!  Will they win?

items.name: The Brutal Betrayal of Ben Grimm

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #42
results.description: With the already brainwashed Thing, the Frightful Four capture and brainwash the Torch! They're on a mission to capture the entire Fantastic Four team!

items.name: To Save You, Why Must I Kill You

results.title: Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #3
results.description: The wedding of Sue and Reed! Note: This 24-page digital comic features the original content from this issue, and does not include the reprints of Fantastic Four #6 & #11 that appeared in the 1965 print edition.

items.name: A Visit with the Fantastic Four

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #43
results.description: When the Frightful Four comes into contact with Reed and Sue, they try to brainwash them as well! Reed performs  surgery on Ben to get him out of his trance and the team must fight together to capture the Frightful Four! The only problem is one of them manages to escape...

items.name: Lo, There Shall Be an Ending

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #44
results.description: When Johnny discovers the escaped Medusa hiding in his car, she demands he drive her out of the city! However, they can't seem to escape the evil Gorgon, who has come for Medusa!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #45
results.description: The First Appearance of the Inhumans!  Johnny meets a girl name Crystal and soon discovers she is Inhuman! Upon meeting her family, Johnny recognizes Medusa and immediately calls the Fantastic Four for backup. Their mysterious leader Black Bolt arrives and the two teams face off!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #46
results.description: While the Fantastic Four are fighting the Inhumans, someone called "The Seeker" arrives. They learn that The Seeker is trying to bring back those who have escaped from the Great Refuge! The Fantastic Four soon recognize another captive of The Seeker... Triton!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #47
results.description: The Fantastic Four meet up with Black Bolt in this issue and have discovered a way to track down the Inhumans!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #48
results.description: The First Appearance of Silver Surfer and Galactus!  Introducing the World-Eater and his enigmatic herald, the Silver Surfer, as the Fantastic Four stand in defense of Earth in one of the most beloved sagas ever told!

textObjects.text: "The Coming of Galactus" begins here! As the Fantastic Four struggle to understand what the Silver Surfer's appearance means, they must steel themselves for what's ahead--Galactus, the devourer of worlds!
The FF were a cosmic quartet from the get-go, but "The Coming of Galacus" solidified their place in the Marvel U. as official masters of all otherworldly problems.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #49
results.description: Behold…Galactus continues!  The Fantastic Four must work together to save the Earth from the evil hands of Galactus! Meanwhile, the Silver Surfer's motives are weakened by the wonders of Alicia Masters and he decides to defeat his master!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #50
results.description: Behold…Galactus concludes!  The Silver Surfer takes on Galactus in an epic battle! Meanwhile, Johnny has received the deadliest weapon of all time-The Ultimate Nullifier!

items.name: The Startling Saga of the Silver Surfer

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #51
results.description: "This man...this monster!" You can't call yourself a fan of Ben Grimm, the ever-lovin' blue-eyed Thing, if you haven't read this issue. 40 years later and it's still one of the greatest Thing stories ever created.

textObjects.text: "This man...this monster!" You can't call yourself a fan of Ben Grimm, the ever-lovin' blue-eyed Thing, if you haven't read this issue. 40 years later and it's still one of the greatest Thing stories ever created.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #52
results.description: The First Appearance of The Black Panther, T'Challa, as well as the nation of Wakanda!  On a mission in the remote wilderness of Wakanda, the Fantastic Four encounter one of Marvel's most iconic heroes...and are bested in battle by the Black Panther!  But how are the Inhumans involved in this earthly encounter?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #53
results.description: The First Appearance of Klaw!  Black Panther explains Wakanda's unique history to the FF. Famed for their reservoirs of the rare and near-indestructible metal Vibranium, Wakanda has secluded itself from civilization to protect their precious ores. The origin story of Black Panther, King of Wakanda!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #54
results.description: Johnny pines to reunite with Crystal while the Inhumans are trapped in the Hidden Land. Will Maximus the Mad finally crack the code to the Inhumans' escape? The Fantastic Four establish a relationship with the Wakandan people, while Johnny Storm embraces his dark side!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #55
results.description: While Reed and Sue make good on their honeymoon, Johnny and Wyatt Wingfoot have a strange encounter with the Silver Surfer! What has brought Galactus' herald to the heights of the Himalayans? Plus, the Thing becomes jealous of Silver Surfer, when he suspects the cosmic being has been making moves on Alicia!

results.title: Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #4
results.description: Johnny and Wyatt reunited with the Fantastic Four at long last! Lockjaw, teleporting dog to the Inhumans, hurtles through dimensions in this exciting annual issue! Johnny Storm vs. the original Human Torch! The Hulk vs. the Thing! The Fantastic Four's greatest moments collected here!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #56
results.description: Ulysses Klaw returns for revenge! Following his defeat in Wakanda at the hands of the FF, Klaw attacks the Baxter Balding armed with sonic super powers! While attempting to escape from the Hidden Land, the Inhumans have an unfortunate accident.

items.name: Klaw, the Murderous Master of Sound

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #57
results.description: The Sandman creates a sand storm all his own, as he escapes from his day in court! The Invisible Woman incapacitated! The Fantastic Four scattered! Chaos reigns supreme, as the Wizard makes his next move. In Latveria, Doctor Doom turns the tables on Silver Surfer.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #58
results.description: After leeching the powers of Silver Surfer, a cosmically-endowed Doctor Doom takes on the FF! A shocking outcome to the team's most significant battle yet! Doom laughs in the face of defeat, and takes on the United States in his latest bid at world domination.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #59
results.description: The Inhumans, free at last! Black Bolt shatters the barrier that has trapped the Inhumans in the Hidden Land. In New York, the Fantastic Four must play military strategist and world savior in the global battle against Doom!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #60
results.description: Doomsday for the Silver Surfer! Robbed of power and imprisoned in Latveria, the Surfer continues to be tortured by Doom's guards.  Will Galactus' herald plot his escape? The Inhumans start to construct their new home following the fall of Attilan!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #61
results.description: Sandman's stalking the FF! And when Mister Fantastic falls into the Negative Zone, his teammates fear for the worst!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #62
results.description: Reed Richards stands alone in the Negative Zone! But his isolation is soon broken by the mighty Blastaar! In the Baxter Building, the Inhumans scramble with the FF to recover their missing leader.

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #63
results.description: Mister Fantastic has been pulled from the Negative Zone...but so has living bomb Blastaar! Sandman and Blastaar rampage against the FF. Good thing Inhuman friends Crystal and Triton are on hand for battle!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #64
results.description: An exotic vacation turned extraterrestrial warfront! Sounds like a typical getaway for the FF- will the team be able to defeat the Kree tech of Sentry #459?

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #65
results.description: The Kree retaliate! After the FF destroys their Sentry, the Kree's Supreme Intelligence unleashes its mightiest warlord. Check out the first appearance of Ronan the Accuser!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #66
results.description: The First Cameo Appearance of Adam Warlock, originally known as Him!  What is the Beehive? From whence did it emerge? A mysterious enclave of scientists kidnaps Alicia Masters.

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #67
results.description: Deep in Lock 41 of the Beehive, Alicia encounters some of the organization's horrifying experiments. 'Him' emerges from a cocoon, intent on the destruction of its creators. The FF pulls off their most daring rescue mission yet!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #5
results.description: Black Panther and the Inhumans storm the Psycho-Man's base, where they must do battle with...Lockjaw!? But that's not all, as Reed and Sue have a stunning announcement that will change the Fantastic Four forever!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

items.name: The Greatest Array of Supporting Characters Ever Assembled in One Issue
[Welcome to the wonderful world of the Fantastic Four]
The Peerless Power of the Silver Surfer

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #68
results.description: A cure for Ben Grimm? Mister Fantastic collaborates with a renowned doctor to reverse the Thing's mutations. But will the procedure go off without a hitch? Johnny introduces his crew to Crystal!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

items.name: His Mission: Destroy the Fantastic Four

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #69
results.description: The Thing goes berserk! After the Mad Thinker's experiment, Ben Grimm goes on a violent spree against his teammates! Will Grimm finally get his chance to eliminate Reed Richards?

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #70
results.description: The FF quashed the Mad Thinker...but now they must contend with a brainwashed Thing! Will Reed, Sue and Johnny be able to go full force against one of their own? All this and the Thinker's android!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #71
results.description: The ever-lovin' Thing is back! No longer possessed by the Mad Thinker, Ben Grimm joins his teammates in battling the Thinker's android! Plus, is this the end of the road for Mr. Fantastic and the Invisible Girl?

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 7 (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #72
results.description: The Silver Surfer has seen enough of humanity to know that it must be destroyed. The Fantastic Four do battle with the cosmic wanderer, but with Sue Richards out of commission, the task at hand seems even more daunting! Will the Surfer see the error of his ways...before it's too late?

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #73
results.description: The FF believes that Daredevil is still inhabited by Doctor Doom, attacking the blind super hero unawares. But little does the team realize, Ol' Hornhead's got some super-powered friends of his own!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #74
results.description: The Silver Surfer has been under the protection of the FF, free from his cosmic responsibilities. But when Galactus unleashes a cyborg to retrieve his former herald, the team is swept up in a battle they don't want to fight!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #75
results.description: Galactus strengthens his resolve to find the missing Silver Surfer...and Reed, Ben and Johnny are trapped in the crossfire! The three heroes must face off against their doppelg'ngers....who have the cosmic powers of Galactus!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #76
results.description: Journey to Sub-Atomica! Reed, Johnny and Ben travel through the Microverse to bring back the Silver Surfer. The crew finds Silver Surfer, all right...and a heap of particulate problems!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #77
results.description: Trapped in the Microverse- at the hands of Psycho-Man! The Silver Surfer may have safely returned to Earth, but Reed, Johnny and Ben are still locked in battle against a megalomaniacal foe. Meanwhile, the threat of Galactus looms ever larger.

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #78
results.description: Reed Richards succeeds in reverting Ben Grimm back to normal...and now, the Thing is no more! But the timing couldn't be worse- the Wizard launches an attack on the FF, and the team is without its primary muscle! Plus, dangerous complications threaten Sue's pregnancy!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #79
results.description: Ben Grimm makes the ultimate sacrifice to save the woman he loves. Will Alicia Masters be safe from the Android Man? Sue's pregnancy raises concern for mother and baby.

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #6
results.description: The baby is coming! With Sue going into labor, Reed must make a perilous journey to obtain Element X, the only thing that can keep the baby safe from the cosmic rays in Sue's body. The bad news - it can only be found in the Negative Zone! The WORSE news? It's in the hands of one of the deadliest beings in any universe - ANNIHILUS!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #80
results.description: The terror of Tomazooma! Reed, Johnny and Ben encounter an android designed after an Indian god while visiting Wyatt Wingfoot's tribe. But Tomazooma is no protector- he's a tyrant!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #81
results.description: Crystal of the Inhumans joins the team! Following Sue's maternity leave, the Fantastic Four...are three. Crystal steps up to the challenge of becoming a full time member, and just in time too- the Wizard's launched an attack on the Baxter Building!

collections.name: Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Vol. 8 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #82
results.description: Maximus the Mad takes on the Fantastic Four...and all of humanity! Crystal seeks permission from her Inhuman family to join the FF in full membership. But upon arriving in the Inhumans' Hidden Land, the team is attacked by Alpha Primitives!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #83
results.description: Reed, Johnny and Ben remain helpless against Maximus and his band of followers. But with the combined might of the Inhuman Royal Family, the FF might be able to save humanity from Maximus' hypno-gun!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #84
results.description: The Fantastic Four infiltrate Latveria on the orders of S.H.I.E.L.D. But given the tyrannical ruler of the country, the team encounters more than they bargained for. The FF versus Doctor Doom and his horde of Servo-Guards!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #85
results.description: Trapped in Latveria, Reed, Johnny, Ben and Crystal become the reluctant guests of Doctor Doom! And the FF is in for some culture shock- especially when Doom unleashes an android army on his own people! This is no diplomatic mission...it's all out war!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #86
results.description: The Invisible Girl returns! After shaking a nasty case of brainwashing, the entire team reunites in Latveria to destroy Doom's robots. And if the FF should fail...Latveria will fall!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #87
results.description: Within the twisted walls of Castle Doom, the team becomes the unwilling participants in Doom's 'power game'. Crystal and Sue are treated to a Latverian banquet...while the men are attacked by flame throwers! The prospect of escape becomes ever bleaker, as the FF fight the machinations of a madman!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #88
results.description: The team's happy reunion is soon interrupted by Mole Man! Plus, will Reed and Sue finally settle on a name for Baby Richards?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #89
results.description: The return of the dreaded Skrulls! But this time, it isn't merely earth that's in dire danger- the target for an unmentionable fate is...the unsuspecting Thing!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #90
results.description: A superhuman Skrull from outer space has landed here on earth. But, he doesn't want to conquer our planet. No, all he wants is...to enslave the Thing!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #91
results.description: See the mighty Thing, enslaved on the planet of the Skrulls! Will the Fantastic Four solve the mystery of their missing teammate...before Ben Grimm faces off in a gladiatorial match?

textObjects.text: By request — the origin of Dr. Doom! (Note: this issue collects stories from Fantastic Four (1961) #1 and Fantastic Four Annual (1963) #2)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #92
results.description: The enslaved Thing must kill...if earth is to survive! Will Ben Grimm comply with his Skrull masters? Even if it means spilling Torgo's blood?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #93
results.description: The Great Games begin at last- and whether he wins or loses...the Thing must die!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #94
results.description: The return of the Frightful Four! And witness the mystic witchcraft of a brand new character! Agatha Harkness' first appearance.

items.name: The Return of the Frightful Four

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #95
results.description: A villain called Monocle! A plot to start World War III! And that's only the beginning!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #96
results.description: The Mad Thinker is back and more powerful than ever, aided by his Androids of Death! 'Nuff said!

items.name: The Mad Thinker and His Androids of Death

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #97
results.description: The FF take a much needed vacation! But while the happy family sunbathes in Florida, a mysterious fish-man is on the loose. Plus, will Reed Richards find the Lost Lagoon of mythic lore?

items.name: The Monster from the Lost Lagoon

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #98
results.description: It's mystery time for the FF again- and what better place than on the moon? Fantasy and suspense...as you like it!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #99
results.description: The Human Torch goes wild as he battles the Inhumans! But what has Johnny so hot-headed? This is the one you've been waiting for!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #100
results.description: The sensational 100th-anniversary issue! Jam-packed with more super-villains than you can count! The Fantastic Four must withstand the latest foil from the Mad Thinker and Puppet Master. And you'll never guess what these villains have up their sleeves!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #101
results.description: The whole team, taken unawares by the Maggia! Will the evil Top Man get ahold of Reed's experiments? The Invisible Girl pulls out all the stops to defend her teammates...and her family!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #102
results.description: Featuring the sensational Sub-Mariner, and the murderous Magneto! What happens when these two foes align themselves for a war on the surface world? Prepare yourselves...for the eve of destruction!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #103
results.description: The Thing battles Namor! Magneto clobbers everyone! And Romita's artwork will flip you out!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #104
results.description: The battle against Atlantis comes to full blows! The Fantastic Four vs. Magneto- vs. Sub-Mariner! And oh, that ending!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #105
results.description: Does the Thing become human at last? Is the FF about to break up? And can anything save them from...the monster in the streets?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #106
results.description: The monster's secret- exposed! Reed's dread decision: who shall die- his wife, or his best friend? A shocker all the way!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #107
results.description: Once again the dreaded Negative Zone threatens to destroy the entire world! But, just when he's needed most...what's happening to the Thing?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #108
results.description: His name is Janus, and he is the key to the most terrifying menace ever to face the Fantastic Four...and the whole human race.

items.name: The Monstrous Mystery of the Nega-Man

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #109
results.description: Annihilus, the most deadly killer of all, waits in the Negative Zone! And our heroes must battle him, as we present...another Marvel death!

collections.name: MARVEL MASTERWORKS: THE FANTASTIC FOUR VOL. 11 HC (Trade Paperback)
MARVEL MASTERWORKS: THE FANTASTIC FOUR VOL. 11 HC (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #110
results.description: It had to happen. The FF couldn't go on forever. If you read no other comic this month, you must not miss "One From Four Leaves Three!" Featuring plenty of witchcraft!

collections.name: MARVEL MASTERWORKS: THE FANTASTIC FOUR VOL. 11 HC (Trade Paperback)
MARVEL MASTERWORKS: THE FANTASTIC FOUR VOL. 11 HC (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #111
results.description: The rampaging Thing turns the city of New York into a blazing battleground, as he attacks the Torch and Mr. Fantastic. And then- enter Bruce Banner!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #112
results.description: Hulk vs. Thing by John Buscema? 'Nuff said.

textObjects.text: Hulk vs. Thing by John Buscema?  'Nuff said.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #113
results.description: The Thing lives! It's either prison or a life of crime for the FF! And then- meet the Overbrain! Guest-starring the Watcher.

MARVEL MASTERWORKS: THE FANTASTIC FOUR VOL. 11 HC (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #114
results.description: At last! This is your chance to learn more about the Over-Mind- one of the most exciting, dangerously different super-foes ever to menace the FF- and all of humanity.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #115
results.description: The origin of the awesome Over-Mind! And Reed Richards turns against the FF!

MARVEL MASTERWORKS: THE FANTASTIC FOUR VOL. 11 HC (Hardcover)

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #116
results.description: Impossible- but true! The new leader of the FF is...Doctor Doom? Plus, the sinister Stranger, and the end of the Over-Mind.

items.name: The Alien, the Ally, and Armageddon

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #117
results.description: Crystal's back...and Diablo's got her! The Human Torch lashes out to save his girlfriend- but will he succeed?

items.name: Lo, There Shall Be An Ending
Lo, There Shall Be an Ending

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #118
results.description: Diablo vs. the Fantastic Four- in a battle that rocks the world! Plus, the Thing in solo action. Don't miss it!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #119
results.description: Torch and the Thing battle alongside the mysterious Black Panther- for a secret that may destroy the world! Plus a mystery super-villain!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #120
results.description: They call their mysterious new foe...the Air-Walker- yet, wait'll you find out who he really is!

items.name: The Horror That Walks on Air

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #121
results.description: Gabriel has blown his horn and the earth faces an apocalypse! The FF battles as never before...but then, you've gotta see that for yourself!

items.name: The Mysterious Mind Blowing Secret of Gabriel

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #122
results.description: Things are just winding up! The Silver Surfer teams up with the FF. But how long can even they survive against the combined power of Gabriel...and Galactus?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #123
results.description: Galactus! The Silver Surfer! The fabulous FF! All cavorting and clashing in perhaps the greatest battle-issue yet!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #124
results.description: From the stars he first came- and now he returns, to menace the earth as never before. The Monster of the Lost Lagoon emerges.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #125
results.description: The secret of the Monster revealed! Can Human Torch and Thing thwart the creature's attack before they, and the planet, perish? Plus, what does this creature really need from Earth?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #126
results.description: The return of the Mole Man! And the FF will never see him coming. Plus, the incredible original of Marvel's First Family re-told.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #127
results.description: The ever-lovin' Thing fights Mole Man alone! But where's the rest of the crew? And, more mind-staggering artwork by John Buscema!

items.name: Where the Sun Dares Not Shine

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #128
results.description: The battle to the finish with Mole Man! And with Mole Man's marriage on the line, this fight's sure to be heated. Will the FF become prisoners in Subterranea?

items.name: Death in a Dark and Lonely Place

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #129
results.description: The Human Torch quits the FF! The Thing embattled! Plus, the return of the Frightful Four- starring a nefarious new recruit.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #130
results.description: Is this the end of the Frightful Four? Plus, the FF trembles at the might of...Thundra! Will this latest recruit hold the key to the Frightful Four's victory?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #131
results.description: The Human Torch and Quicksilver battle each other, and a maddening new menace, in the land of the uncanny Inhumans! Will Human Torch be accepted by Crystal's family?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #132
results.description: The Inhumans take center stage, as the ominous behemoth called Omega emerges! Plus, the most shock-laden epilogue you won't want to miss.

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #133
results.description: The Thing- vs. the super-powered bombshell named Thundra! Will this issue spell the end for Ben and Alicia?

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #134
results.description: What's happened to Agatha Harkness? The FF answer a distress call, only to find Agatha's home destroyed. Meanwhile, Franklin's behavior raises red flags for Sue, but there's no time to act- the Dragon Man attacks!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #135
results.description: Reed, Sue, Franklin and Medusa have been kidnapped by mad scientist Gregory Gideon! But for what purpose? If the Human Torch doesn't arrive soon, it could be a disastrous ending for Marvel's First Family!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #136
results.description: Having escaped Gideon's clutches, the Fantastic Four must now take on the Wild Ones Gang! But how does Slugger Johnson fit into this madness? And finally, an ending where the FF don't win!

results.title: Fantastic Four (1961) #137
results.description: The Shaper of Worlds has re-written reality! The FF can't make heads or tails of this strange, new world hatched from the mind of a crazed villain. Plus, there's no sense to be had with the Wild Ones brainwashing the team!
